# GEM Z вЂ” Phase 1: PostgreSQL Database Schema

The schema is written to [f:/Gem Z/database/schema.sql](file:///f:/Gem%20Z/database/schema.sql).  
It covers **7 modules**, **~50 tables**, and is designed for strict financial accuracy, scalability, and AI-readiness.

---

## Module Breakdown

### 1 В· Users & Roles

| Table | Purpose |
|---|---|
| `users` | Single source of truth for all roles. `role` enum: `trainee`, `trainer`, `gym_admin`, `store_admin`, `super_admin` |
| `trainee_profiles` | Extended stats: height, weight, body fat, QR token, streak, points |
| `trainer_profiles` | Bio, specializations, certifications, rating, commission % |

> [!NOTE]
> The referral system is built directly into `users.referral_code` (auto-generated 8-char hash) and `users.referred_by_user_id`.

---

### 2 В· Business Entities

| Table | Purpose |
|---|---|
| `gyms` | Gym entity with configurable `platform_fee_pct` (default 15%) |
| `gym_branches` | Multi-branch with PostGIS `GEOGRAPHY(POINT)` for geolocation/geofencing |
| `gym_pricing_rules` | Off-peak / flash sale discounts by day-of-week + time range |
| `stores` | Store entity with configurable fee (default 17.5%) |
| `store_products` | Product catalog with SKU, stock, category, and discount |

---

### 3 В· Financial Ledger вљ пёЏ

> [!IMPORTANT]
> **Double-Entry Design** вЂ” Every payment creates exactly two `ledger_entries` rows: one `debit` (from buyer's wallet) and one `credit` (to seller's wallet), plus a platform fee split entry. The `available_bal` column has a `CHECK (>= 0)` constraint making overdrafts impossible at the DB level.

| Table | Purpose |
|---|---|
| `wallets` | Polymorphic вЂ” owned by `user`, `gym`, `store`, or `platform` |
| `transactions` | One row per business event. Stores gateway ref, type, status |
| `ledger_entries` | The immutable double-entry lines. Includes `running_balance` snapshot |
| `withdrawal_requests` | Payout requests to Fawry / Instapay / Vodafone Cash / bank |

**Revenue split example** (1,000 EGP gym sub, 15% fee):

```
DEBIT  trainee_wallet     1,000 EGP
CREDIT gym_wallet           850 EGP  (pending в†’ available after settlement window)
CREDIT platform_wallet       150 EGP
```

---

### 4 В· Subscriptions & Orders

| Table | Purpose |
|---|---|
| `gym_subscription_plans` | Can be gym-wide or branch-specific, with freeze allowance |
| `gym_subscriptions` | Trainee в†” plan link, stores `discount_applied` for off-peak pricing |
| `trainer_subscription_plans` | Trainer packages (sessions count, online/offline) |
| `trainer_subscriptions` | Trainee в†” trainer link |
| `attendance_logs` | QR / NFC check-in/out per branch |
| `orders` | Store purchase header |
| `order_items` | Line-items with quantity, unit price, subtotal |

---

### 5 В· Fitness & AI

| Table | Purpose |
|---|---|
| `muscle_groups` | Lookup: chest, back, legs, etc. |
| `exercises` | Full library with video URL, difficulty, calories/min |
| `workout_plans` / `workout_days` / `workout_exercises` | Hierarchical plan structure |
| `medical_reports` | OCR upload в†’ parsed JSONB for AI input |
| `ai_diet_plans` | AI-generated plan with macro targets and allergen flags |
| `meals` | Day-by-day meals with `alternatives` JSONB (smart swaps) |
| `daily_logs` | Trainee self-tracking: calories, water, steps, sleep, weight |
| `wearable_sync_logs` | Apple Watch, Garmin, Google Fit raw sync data |
| `form_correction_sessions` | MediaPipe analysis results: joint angles, score, issues |

---

### 6 В· Social & Gamification

| Table | Purpose |
|---|---|
| `posts` | Timeline posts (update, progress photo, achievement, Q&A, video) |
| `post_comments` | Threaded replies via `parent_id` self-reference |
| `post_likes` / `comment_likes` | Composite PK prevents duplicate likes |
| `follows` | Follower graph with self-loop guard |
| `badges` | Configurable via `trigger_rule` JSONB (`streak_days`, `milestone_kg`, вЂ¦) |
| `user_badges` | Unique constraint prevents duplicate awards |
| `leaderboard_snapshots` | Scoped (global / city / gym) + period snapshots |
| `referral_rewards` | Discount codes with expiry and use-count cap |
| `notifications` | Typed push/in-app notifications |

---

### 7 В· Support & Admin

| Table | Purpose |
|---|---|
| `support_tickets` | Priority + status workflow with admin assignment |
| `ticket_replies` | Internal/external thread, supports agent notes |

