## Entity Relationship Overview

```mermaid
erDiagram
    users ||--o{ trainee_profiles : "has"
    users ||--o{ trainer_profiles : "has"
    users ||--o{ wallets : "owns"
    users ||--o{ posts : "writes"
    users ||--o{ gym_subscriptions : "buys"
    users ||--o{ orders : "places"

    gyms ||--|{ gym_branches : "has"
    gyms ||--o{ gym_subscription_plans : "offers"
    gym_branches ||--o{ attendance_logs : "records"

    stores ||--|{ store_products : "lists"
    orders ||--|{ order_items : "contains"

    transactions ||--|{ ledger_entries : "splits into"
    wallets ||--o{ ledger_entries : "receives"

    users ||--o{ ai_diet_plans : "gets"
    ai_diet_plans ||--|{ meals : "contains"
    medical_reports }o--|| ai_diet_plans : "informs"

    posts ||--o{ post_comments : "has"
    posts ||--o{ post_likes : "receives"
    users ||--o{ follows : "initiates"
    users ||--o{ user_badges : "earns"
```

---

## Key Design Decisions

| Decision | Rationale |
|---|---|
| `NUMERIC(19,4)` for all money | Avoids floating-point rounding errors completely |
| `uuid_generate_v4()` as PKs | Prevents enumeration attacks; safe for distributed systems |
| PostGIS `GEOGRAPHY(POINT)` | Enables radius queries for nearby gym search natively in SQL |
| Polymorphic `wallets.owner_type` | Single wallet table for users, gyms, stores, and platform |
| Immutable `ledger_entries` | Never UPDATE/DELETE вЂ” only INSERT new correction entries |
| `CHECK (available_bal >= 0)` | DB-level overdraft protection, cannot be bypassed by code |
| `trigger_rule JSONB` on badges | New badge types added without schema migrations |

